Note on applying CC BY-NC-ND to source code
-------------------------------------------
Creative Commons itself notes that CC licenses are NOT recommended for software,
and that licensors should use software-specific licenses (MIT, Apache 2.0,
GPL, etc.) when the work is primarily code. The TechTeaStudio copyright
holders have nevertheless chosen this license as the most restrictive option
that still permits viewing and redistribution of the source. Commercial use
and derivative works (including forks and modifications redistributed under a
different name) are NOT permitted without explicit written permission from
TechTeaStudio.

